channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: AOC demands Senate Democrats investigate reports of Jan. 6 flags flown at Supreme Court Justice Alito's home
item.description: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez called on Senate Democrats to investigate reports of flags linked to the Jan. 6 riot at Justice Samuel Alito's homes.

item.title: Trump Says He Will Get Putin to Free Jailed US Reporter Gershkovich
item.description: Donald Trump posted on social media he will use his relationship with Russian President Vladimir Putin to get Wall Street reporter Evan Gershkovich freed from a Russian prison.

item.title: WATCH: Tim Kaine Gives Insane Commentary on 'Butcher of Tehran' When Pressed on WH 'Condolences'
Trump says WSJ reporter Evan Gershkovich 'will be released almost immediately' after November election
item.description: Former President Trump says WSJ reporter Evan Gershkovich, who is being detained in Russia, will be released following the election later this year.

item.title: Will Scharf to Newsmax: N.Y. Judge Should Have Recused Himself
item.description: The judge overseeing the Trump case in New York should have recused himself due to conflicts of interest, Trump attorney Will Scharf told Newsmax Wednesday.

item.title: You're FIRED! Portland Voters Hand Soft-on-Crime, Soros-Backed DA His Walking Papers
New batch of 'morally bankrupt' college administrators to be grilled over campus antisemitism by House
item.description: The House Committee on Education and the Workforce is preparing to grill leaders from Northwestern, UCLA and Rutgers over their handling of campus antisemitism.

item.title: RFK Jr. Senior Adviser Departs Campaign
item.description: Angela Stanton King, a senior adviser to Robert F. Kennedy Jr.'s independent campaign for president, announced she was leaving his team due to an "increasingly hateful and divisive atmosphere."

item.title: Winning: Patrick Mahomes, Andy Reid Show the Way When Asked About the Harrison Butker Nontroversy
12 state attorneys general challenge blue states' 'radical' climate policies impacting others
item.description: Twelve states are petitioning the Supreme Court to rule on blue-state policies they claim are forcing other states to follow their left-wing climate change agenda.

item.title: Peak Insights Poll: Missouri Governor's Race Is Tightening
item.description: A new Peak Insights poll shows the race for Republican nomination for Governor of Mo. is a dead heat, with Jay Ashcroft, the Missouri Secretary of State and son of former Governor John Ashcroft, at 22%, and Mike Kehoe, the Lieutenant Governor of Missouri, at 20%.

item.title: Megyn Kelly Schools Bill Maher on Trump, J6, Biden and the Border in Epic Interview
Biden outpaces Trump with 200 confirmed judges, cementing impact on courts
item.description: Biden hit a milestone of 200 judges appointed to the federal bench on Wednesday, outpacing Trump's record of judicial appointments at the same point.

item.title: CPD's Fahrenkopf to Newsmax: Many Questions on Biden-Trump Debates
item.description: Now that President Joe Biden and former President Donald Trump are bypassing the typical road taken for presidential debates during an election season, a lot of questions remain on how they will be managed, Frank J. Fahrenkopf Jr., told Newsmax on Wednesday.
